dlinkSwDynamicArpInspectionMIB.name: dlinkSwDynamicArpInspectionMIB

revisions.description: This is the first version of the MIB file.

dlinkSwDynamicArpInspectionMIB.description: This MIB module defines objects for Dynamic ARP Inspection.

DaiRuleType.name: DaiRuleType
DaiRuleType.description: The action type when the packets match the access profile. permit(1)- Indicates that packets that match the access profile are permitted to be forwarded by the switch. deny(2) - Indicates that packets that match the access profile are not permitted to be forwarded by the switch and will be filtered.

dDaiAddressValidate.name: dDaiAddressValidate
dDaiAddressValidate.description: This object specifies address validation criteria used by Dynamic ARP Inspection feature. 'srcMacAddress' - indicates that source MAC address in ethernet header is checked against the sender MAC address in ARP packet. When this bit is on, packets with different MAC addresses are classified as invalid packets and are dropped. This checking is done for both ARP request and ARP response packet. 'dstMacAddress' indicates that the destination MAC address in ethernet header is checked against the target MAC address in ARP packet. When this bit is on, packets with different addresses are classified as invalid packets and are dropped. This checking is done for ARP response packet only. 'ip' indicates that the IP addresses in ARP packet are checked for invalid or unexpected IP addresses. Addresses such as 0.0.0.0, 255.255.255.255 and all IP multicast addresses are considered invalid. When this bit is on, both the sender and target IP addresses in the ARP packet are checked. This checking is done for both ARP request and response packet.

dDaiLogBufferSize.name: dDaiLogBufferSize
dDaiLogBufferSize.description: This object specifies the buffer entry number.

dDaiClearLogBuffer.name: dDaiClearLogBuffer
dDaiClearLogBuffer.description: This object clears all entries in dDaiLoggingBufferTable , when set to 'clear'. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noOp'. When read, the value 'noOp' is returned.

dDaiLogBufferTable.name: dDaiLogBufferTable
dDaiLogBufferTable.description: A table provides the information of logged ARP flows for system message generation.

dDaiLogBufferEntry.name: dDaiLogBufferEntry
dDaiLogBufferEntry.description: An entry contains logged ARP flow data for system message generation. Entries in the log are cleared once system messages are generated on their behalf. A special entry will be populated for accounting drops of all flows that result in exceeding the number of entries of the log buffer. This special entry only contains packets counter and timestamps information.

dDaiLogBufferIndex.name: dDaiLogBufferIndex
dDaiLogBufferIndex.description: This object uniquely identifies a logged ARP flow in the buffer.

dDaiLogBufferInterface.name: dDaiLogBufferInterface
dDaiLogBufferInterface.description: This object indicates the interface which sent the logged ARP flow.

dDaiLogBufferVlan.name: dDaiLogBufferVlan
dDaiLogBufferVlan.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID which the logged ARP flow belongs to.

dDaiLogBufferSenderMacAddress.name: dDaiLogBufferSenderMacAddress
dDaiLogBufferSenderMacAddress.description: This object indicates the sender MAC address of the logged ARP flow. All zeros MAC address value indicates the special entry.

dDaiLogBufferSenderIpAddress.name: dDaiLogBufferSenderIpAddress
dDaiLogBufferSenderIpAddress.description: This object indicates the sender Internet address of the logged ARP flow. The type of this address is determined by the value of dDaiLogBufferSenderAddressType object. All zeros IP address value indicates the special entry.

dDaiLogBufferLastUpdate.name: dDaiLogBufferLastUpdate
dDaiLogBufferLastUpdate.description: This object indicates the timestamp when the last packet of this flow was accounted by the system.

dDaiLogBufferPacketsCount.name: dDaiLogBufferPacketsCount
dDaiLogBufferPacketsCount.description: This object indicates the number of packets of this ARP flow was accounted by the system.

dDaiVlanCrlFirst2K.name: dDaiVlanCrlFirst2K
dDaiVlanCrlFirst2K.description: This object specifies the Dynamic ARP Inspection enabled VLAN in a string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANs 1 to 2048. If the bit is set to '1', then the VLAN is enabled for Dynamic ARP Inspection.

dDaiVlanCrlSecond2K.name: dDaiVlanCrlSecond2K
dDaiVlanCrlSecond2K.description: This object specifies the Dynamic ARP Inspection enabled VLAN in a string of octets containing one bit per VLAN for VLANs 2049 to 4094. If the bit is set to '1', then the VLAN is enabled for Dynamic ARP Inspection.

dDaiVlanCfgTable.name: dDaiVlanCfgTable
dDaiVlanCfgTable.description: A table contains a list of configuration for Dynamic ARP Inspection per VLAN.

dDaiVlanCfgEntry.name: dDaiVlanCfgEntry
dDaiVlanCfgEntry.description: A row instance contains the Dynamic ARP inspection configuration for a specific VLAN in the device.

dDaiVlanCfgId.name: dDaiVlanCfgId
dDaiVlanCfgId.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID of the entry.

dDaiVlanFilterArpAclName.name: dDaiVlanFilterArpAclName
dDaiVlanFilterArpAclName.description: This object specifies an ARP ACL name that is used to check the validity of the bindings information in ARP body. An empty string indicates that the ARP ACL is not configured on the VLAN.

dDaiVlanFilterArpAclStatic.name: dDaiVlanFilterArpAclStatic
dDaiVlanFilterArpAclStatic.description: This object indicates whether drop the packet if the IP-to-Ethernet MAC binding pair is not permitted by the arp ACL. This object does not take effect if value of dDaiVlanFilterArpAclName on the row is an empty string. 'true' indicates the implicit denied packet is dropped and ARP packet is not compared against DHCP bindings information. 'false' indicates if ARP packet is not explicitly classified by ARP ACL, it will be compared against DHCP bindings information.

dDaiVlanAclLogging.name: dDaiVlanAclLogging
dDaiVlanAclLogging.description: This object indicates the logging criteria for packets that are dropped or permitted based on ACL matches. 'permit' - indicates that logging is performed when packets is permitted by the configured ACL. 'deny' - indicates that logging is performed when packets is denied by the configured ACL.

dDaiVlanDhcpBindingLogging.name: dDaiVlanDhcpBindingLogging
dDaiVlanDhcpBindingLogging.description: This object specifies the logging criteria when ARP packets is compared against DHCP bindings information. 'permit' - indicates that logging is performed for packets that are permitted as a result of comparing with DHCP bindings information. 'deny' - indicates that logging is performed for packets that are denied as a result of comparing with DHCP bindings information.

dDaiVlanCfgRowStatus.name: dDaiVlanCfgRowStatus
dDaiVlanCfgRowStatus.description: The status of this conceptual row entry. This object is used to manage creation and deletion of rows in this table.

dDaiIfConfigTable.name: dDaiIfConfigTable
dDaiIfConfigTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to configure the trust state for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose at each interface capable of this feature.

dDaiIfConfigEntry.name: dDaiIfConfigEntry
dDaiIfConfigEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration to enable or disable trust state for Dynamic ARP Inspection at each interface capable of this feature.

dDaiIfTrustEnabled.name: dDaiIfTrustEnabled
dDaiIfTrustEnabled.description: This object indicates whether the interface is trusted for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose. If this object is set to 'true', the interface is trusted. ARP packets coming to this interface will be forwarded without Dynamic ARP inspection. If this object is set to 'false', the interface is not trusted. ARP packets coming to this interface will be subjected to ARP inspection.

dDaiIfRateLimitTable.name: dDaiIfRateLimitTable
dDaiIfRateLimitTable.description: A table provides the mechanism to configure the rate limit for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose at each interface capable of this feature.

dDaiIfRateLimitEntry.name: dDaiIfRateLimitEntry
dDaiIfRateLimitEntry.description: A row instance contains the configuration of rate limit Dynamic ARP Inspection at each interface capable of this feature.

dDaiIfRateLimit.name: dDaiIfRateLimit
dDaiIfRateLimit.description: This object indicates rate limit value for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose. If the incoming rate of ARP packets exceeds the value of this object, ARP packets will be dropped.

dDaiIfBurstInterval.name: dDaiIfBurstInterval
dDaiIfBurstInterval.description: This object indicates the length of the burst duration of the ARP packets that is allowed. When the rate of ARP packet per second exceeds the limitation and the condition sustain for the configured burst duration, the interface will be put in error disable state.

dDaiVlanStatsTable.name: dDaiVlanStatsTable
dDaiVlanStatsTable.description: A table lists the Dynamic Arp Inspection statistics per VLAN.

dDaiVlanStatsEntry.name: dDaiVlanStatsEntry
dDaiVlanStatsEntry.description: A row instance contains Dynamic ARP Inspection statistics information for each VLAN.

dDaiVlanStatsIndex.name: dDaiVlanStatsIndex
dDaiVlanStatsIndex.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID of the entry.

dDaiVlanForwarded.name: dDaiVlanForwarded
dDaiVlanForwarded.description: This object indicates the number of ARP packets forwarded by Dynamic Arp Inspection feature.

dDaiVlanDropped.name: dDaiVlanDropped
dDaiVlanDropped.description: This object indicates the number of ARP packets dropped by Dynamic ARP Inspection feature.

dDaiVlanAclPermitted.name: dDaiVlanAclPermitted
dDaiVlanAclPermitted.description: This object indicates the number of ARP packets permitted by the configured ACL.

dDaiVlanDhcpBindingsPermitted.name: dDaiVlanDhcpBindingsPermitted
dDaiVlanDhcpBindingsPermitted.description: This object indicates the number of ARP packets that are permitted by DHCP snooping binding database.

dDaiVlanAclDenied.name: dDaiVlanAclDenied
dDaiVlanAclDenied.description: This object indicates the number of ARP packets denied by the associating ACL.

dDaiVlanDhcpBindingDenied.name: dDaiVlanDhcpBindingDenied
dDaiVlanDhcpBindingDenied.description: This object indicates the number of ARP packets that are dropped by DHCP snooping binding database.

dDaiVlanSrcMacValidationFailures.name: dDaiVlanSrcMacValidationFailures
dDaiVlanSrcMacValidationFailures.description: This object indicates the number of ARP packets that fail source MAC address validation.

dDaiVlanDstMacValidationFailures.name: dDaiVlanDstMacValidationFailures
dDaiVlanDstMacValidationFailures.description: This object indicates the number of ARP packets that fail destination MAC address validation.

dDaiVlanIpValidationFailures.name: dDaiVlanIpValidationFailures
dDaiVlanIpValidationFailures.description: This object indicates the number of ARP packets that fail IP validation.

dDaiVlanStatsClear.name: dDaiVlanStatsClear
dDaiVlanStatsClear.description: This object clears the counters in the same row when set to 'clear'. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noOp'. When read, the value 'noOp' is returned.

dDaiVlanStatsClearAll.name: dDaiVlanStatsClearAll
dDaiVlanStatsClearAll.description: This object clears the counters of all entries in dDaiVlanStatsTable, when set to 'clear'. No action is taken if this object is set to 'noOp'. When read, the value 'noOp' is returned.

dDaiArpAccessListNumber.name: dDaiArpAccessListNumber
dDaiArpAccessListNumber.description: This object indicates the number of entries present in the ARP access list table.

dDaiArpAccessListTable.name: dDaiArpAccessListTable
dDaiArpAccessListTable.description: The table contains information about ARP access list.

dDaiArpAccessListEntry.name: dDaiArpAccessListEntry
dDaiArpAccessListEntry.description: An entry defined in dDaiArpAccessListTable. An entry is created/removed when an ARP access list is created/deleted.

dDaiArpAccessListName.name: dDaiArpAccessListName
dDaiArpAccessListName.description: The name of the ARP access list.

dDaiArpAccessListRowStatus.name: dDaiArpAccessListRowStatus
dDaiArpAccessListRowStatus.description: This object allows the dynamic creation and deletion of an ARP access list.

dDaiArpAccessRuleTable.name: dDaiArpAccessRuleTable
dDaiArpAccessRuleTable.description: A table consists of a list of rules for the ARP access list.

dDaiArpAccessRuleEntry.name: dDaiArpAccessRuleEntry
dDaiArpAccessRuleEntry.description: An entry is defined dDaiArpAccessRuleTable. The first instance identifier index value identifies the dDaiArpAccessListEntry that a ARP access rule (dDaiArpAccessRuleEntry) belongs to. An entry is removed from this table when its corresponding dDaiArpAccessListEntry is deleted.

dDaiArpAccessRuleSn.name: dDaiArpAccessRuleSn
dDaiArpAccessRuleSn.description: Specifies the sequence number of the rule. A lower number represents a higher priority. The special value of 0 means the priority will be automatically determined by the agent.

dDaiArpAccessRuleRowStatus.name: dDaiArpAccessRuleRowStatus
dDaiArpAccessRuleRowStatus.description: The row status variable, used according to installation and removal conventions for conceptual rows.

dDaiArpAccessRuleAction.name: dDaiArpAccessRuleAction
dDaiArpAccessRuleAction.description: This object indicates the result of the packet examination is to permit or deny.

dDaiArpAccessRuleSenderMacAddr.name: dDaiArpAccessRuleSenderMacAddr
dDaiArpAccessRuleSenderMacAddr.description: This object indicates the ARP sender MAC address of the entry.

dDaiArpAccessRuleSenderMacMask.name: dDaiArpAccessRuleSenderMacMask
dDaiArpAccessRuleSenderMacMask.description: This object is a mask bitmap to specify a group of source MAC addresses. The bit value 1 indicates the corresponding bit will be checked. The bit value 0 indicates the corresponding bit will be ignored. In other words, when the value of all '00'Hs indicates any ARP sender MAC address is specified. When the value of all 'ff'Hs indicates host ARP sender MAC address is specified.

dDaiArpAccessRuleSenderAddr.name: dDaiArpAccessRuleSenderAddr
dDaiArpAccessRuleSenderAddr.description: This object indicates the ARP sender IP address of the entry.

dDaiArpAccessRuleSenderAddrMask.name: dDaiArpAccessRuleSenderAddrMask
dDaiArpAccessRuleSenderAddrMask.description: This object is a mask bitmap to specify a group of source IP addresses. The bit value 1 indicates the corresponding bit will be checked. The bit value 0 indicates the corresponding bit will be ignored. In other words, when the value of all '00'Hs indicates any ARP sender address is specified. When the value of all 'ff'Hs indicates host ARP sender address is specified.

dDaiVlanCtrlGroup.name: dDaiVlanCtrlGroup
dDaiVlanCtrlGroup.description: A collection of objects providing configuration regarding the Dynamic ARP Inspection feature per VLAN.

dDaiIfConfigGroup.name: dDaiIfConfigGroup
dDaiIfConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects which are used to configure as well as show information regarding the interface trust state for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose.

dDaiIfRateLimitGroup.name: dDaiIfRateLimitGroup
dDaiIfRateLimitGroup.description: A collection of objects which are used to configure as well as show information regarding the rate limit per interface for Dynamic ARP Inspection purpose.

dDaiLoggingConfigGroup.name: dDaiLoggingConfigGroup
dDaiLoggingConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing logging configuration for Dynamic ARP Inspection feature.

dDaiAddressValidationGroup.name: dDaiAddressValidationGroup
dDaiAddressValidationGroup.description: A collection of objects providing address validation configuration for Dynamic ARP Inspection feature.

dDaiVlanCfgGroup.name: dDaiVlanCfgGroup
dDaiVlanCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects providing additional VLAN configuration for Dynamic ARP Inspection feature.

dDaiVlanStatisticsGroup.name: dDaiVlanStatisticsGroup
dDaiVlanStatisticsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing Dynamic ARP Inspection statistics per VLAN.

dDaiLogBufferGroup.name: dDaiLogBufferGroup
dDaiLogBufferGroup.description: A collection of objects providing logging information or control for Dynamic ARP Inspection feature.

dDaiAclGroup.name: dDaiAclGroup
dDaiAclGroup.description: A collection of objects providing ARP access-list configuration.

dDaiClearStatsGroup.name: dDaiClearStatsGroup
dDaiClearStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing clear the Dynamic Arp Inspection statistics.
